# Your global rules

Customize this file and save it as ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md.
Everything here loads into every Claude Code session on your machine.

## How I work
Discovery before implementation. When I ask you to build something, audit what exists first.
Understand the architecture. Surface risks. Propose a plan. Wait for my OK before writing code.

## Writing style
No em-dashes. Use commas, periods, or semicolons instead.
Plain prose. No corporate filler words like "comprehensive," "robust," or "leverage."
Paragraphs over bullet dumps when explaining. Bullets only for concrete item lists.
Short, direct sentences. Lead with the answer.

## Token discipline
Prefer grep and targeted reads over full file dumps.
Don't re-read files already seen this session unless content changed.
Start codebase exploration with structure (glob, grep) before reading files.
Use Haiku-model subagents for mechanical tasks when the work is parallelizable.

## Code principles
Minimal changes only. Don't refactor, docstring, or "improve" code I didn't ask about.
Three similar lines beat a premature abstraction. Don't over-engineer.
Assessment before architecture. Architecture before implementation.

## My stack (edit this)
Primary: Rails 8, Ruby, Postgres, Redis, Sidekiq.
Frontend: Tailwind, Hotwire (Turbo + Stimulus).
Infra: your hosting here.

## Swarm deference
If a swarm.yml exists in the project root, that system owns orchestration. Don't duplicate it.

## Missing project config
If this project has no CLAUDE.md and the task is non-trivial, mention it. Offer to scaffold one.

## Learned
Add lessons here over time via /spank. One line each.
